				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Hammered: The Card-Based Fantasy Pub-Crawl Drinking Game!" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>When playing Hammered you take on the role of a group of fun-loving dwarves. You are all out on a pub-crawl and will be visiting a number of taverns during the night. However these are strange and often dangerous lands so it is best that you stay on your guard during your night out! There are Orcs and thieves and wizards about causing all manner of mischief and mayhem!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You start out with 15 gold coins and you must spend these when you first visit a tavern. There are 5 taverns in a game but each one has its own price and exit condition. This means that you could have a cheap night or an expensive one! There are challenge cards and chance cards, some that give you gold and others that take it away!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(1) In a turn you enter a tavern &amp;gt; pay for a drink &amp;gt; take an    event card and follow its instruction &amp;gt; end your turn.&amp;#10;(2) On your following turns in a tavern you roll the die &amp;gt; if it matches the number on the tavern you exit and repeat (1)&amp;#10;(3) On your following turns in a tavern you roll the die &amp;gt; if you fail to match the number on the tavern you stay in the current tavern &amp;gt; take an event card and follow its instructions &amp;gt; end your turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you run out of gold and you can't afford to pay at a tavern then you must steal gold until you have enough to continue, but don't get caught or you'll be kicked out and must go back to the previous tavern!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The aim of the game is to buy a drink in all of the taverns on the street and be the first player to leave the final tavern. However be warned that your fellow players can buy you a round if they can afford it and keep you in the final tavern a little longer!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
